00:50:56.774 --> 00:51:00.594
Jemal, this year's awardee, is truly among the most influential voices in

841
00:51:00.614 --> 00:51:03.994
oncology. And in his lecture, he provided numerous

842
00:51:04.054 --> 00:51:07.754
examples of how cancer surveillance data can promote cancer

843
00:51:07.834 --> 00:51:11.274
prevention and control. And the one that I will highlight here

844
00:51:11.914 --> 00:51:15.564
is his recent paper in "Cancer Discovery" demonstrating the powerful

845
00:51:15.714 --> 00:51:19.434
impact that legislation and policy can have on reducing cancer

846
00:51:19.454 --> 00:51:23.014
disparities. So what he showed here is that compared to cancer

