00:51:38.094 --> 00:51:42.074
patients. So I think this makes it very clear that the current threat that we

852
00:51:42.154 --> 00:51:46.094
have of rolling back support for healthcare in our country could have

853
00:51:46.134 --> 00:51:50.014
a devastating effect on curtailing and even reversing the progress that we

854
00:51:50.094 --> 00:51:51.274
have made in recent years.

855
00:51:53.514 --> 00:51:57.354
Another highly engaging session, I think a lot of the participants had a lot of

856
00:51:57.394 --> 00:52:00.844
fun with this one, presented the state-of-the-art in leveraging

857
00:52:00.914 --> 00:52:04.894
geospatial tools, methods, and data to address issues related

858
00:52:04.934 --> 00:52:07.594
to cancer incidence, outcomes, and disparities.

859
00:52:07.834 --> 00:52:11.314
These approaches are now being actively used to identify cancer

860
00:52:11.374 --> 00:52:15.294
