900
00:54:31.402 --> 00:54:33.642
prostate cancer in African men.

901
00:54:34.862 --> 00:54:38.602
Two of the key results that she presented are associations between geographic

902
00:54:38.682 --> 00:54:42.362
area and unique prostate cancer genomic subtypes, as well

903
00:54:42.502 --> 00:54:44.622
as in blood metal concentrations.

904
00:54:45.042 --> 00:54:48.562
A major emphasis of this talk was the potential of really

905
00:54:48.572 --> 00:54:52.222
leveraging genomic and exposomic science together to

906
00:54:52.302 --> 00:54:56.002
integrate environmental features with genetic and tumor information to

907
00:54:56.062 --> 00:54:59.352
ultimately reduce prostate cancer incidence and improve survival.

908
00:55:00.662 --> 00:55:04.422
The last area that I'm going to cover is advances in

909
00:55:04.462 --> 00:55:05.942
community outreach and engagement,

910
00:55:06.982 --> 00:55:10.152
where here the question is: how do we meaningfully advance bi-directional

911
00:55:10.162 --> 00:55:13.802
engagement with the communities we serve to expand our

